article.headline: James Madison 99, Towson 68
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Andrey Semenov scored 20 points and Rayshawn Goins had a double-double to lead James Madison to a 99-68 victory over Towson on Wednesday night. Goins had 16 points and 10 rebounds for his fifth double-double of the season as the Dukes (12-3, 2-1 Colonial Athletic Association) won their sixth consecutive game. They also improved to 7-0 at home this season. James Madison shot 59.1 percent from the field (13 of 22) in the first half and improved that to 71 percent in the second (22 of 31) to finish at 66 percent for the game (35 of 53). The Dukes also shot 57.1 percent from the 3-point line (12 of 21) and 85 percent from the foul line (17 of 20). Twelve players scored for James Madison, including Trevon Flores, who tied his career high with 11 points. Rashawn Polk led Towson (4-9, 0-3) with 20 points. Josh Brown added 18 points and Isaiah Philmore had 11.
